g, Yong, Byung, Chang, Dong, Hyun, Jae, Jee, Jong, Jong Hun, Jong Hyun, Moon Hee, Jung Suk, Sang, Seok, Seung, Soon, Sungtae, Taeyong.","German: metonymic occupational name for a sealer of weights and measures, from Middle High German <i>hāme</i> ‘(standard) measure’.","Korean: variant of   Ham  ."]},{"name":"Hams","meanings":["English: variant of   Ham   with plural <i>-s</i> or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Johann","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Vernacular form of   Johannes ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Johann Ham was born in 1520, in Prussia, Germany. He had at least 1 son. He died in 1610, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 90."},"et":{"1520–1610":"1520–1610","1545–1591":"1545–1591","1545":"1545","1610":"1610","1520":"1520","1591":"1591","Prussia, Germany":"Preußen, Saksamaa","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1520–1610":"1520–1610","1545–1591":"1545–1591","1545":"1545","1610":"1610","1520":"1520","1591":"1591","Prussia, Germany":"Preußen, Saksa","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1520–1610":"1520–1610","1545–1591":"1545–1591","1545":"1545","1610":"1610","1520":"1520","1591":"1591","Prussia, Germany":"Prusse, Allemagne","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Johann Ham est né en 1520, à Prusse, Allemagne. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1610, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 90 ans."},"de":{"1520–1610":"1520–1610","1545–1591":"1545–1591","1545":"1545","1610":"1610","1520":"1520","1591":"1591","Prussia, Germany":"Preußen, Deutschland","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Johann Ham wurde 1520 in Preußen, Deutschland geboren. Er hatte mind